---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Growth Room"
  description="Privacy Policy for Growth Room — how we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a] text-zinc-300">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 sm:px-8">

      <a href="/" class="mb-10 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-zinc-500 hover:text-[#C9A44A] transition">
        ← Back to Growth Room
      </a>

      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Last updated: June 4, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose-policy mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            Growth Room ("we", "us", or "our") operates the website <strong class="text-zinc-200">growthroom.co</strong> and sells
            digital products and online courses through <strong class="text-zinc-200">afilma.com</strong>. This Privacy Policy
            explains how we collect, use, store, and share your personal data when you interact with our website,
            join our waitlist, or purchase our products.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">2. Data We Collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Contact information</strong> — name, email address, and phone number when you submit a form.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Marketing data</strong> — ad budget range, business type, and other fields in our application forms.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Usage data</strong> — pages visited, time on site, clicks, and browser/device information collected via cookies and analytics tools (Google Analytics, Meta Pixel).</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Payment data</strong> — processed exclusively by <strong class="text-zinc-200">afilma.com</strong>; we do not store card or banking details on our servers.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>To respond to your inquiries and process your application to Growth Room.</li>
            <li>To send transactional emails (purchase confirmation, access to courses).</li>
            <li>To send marketing communications — you may unsubscribe at any time.</li>
            <li>To measure and improve our advertising campaigns (Google Ads, Meta Ads).</li>
            <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <p>
            We use cookies and similar technologies for analytics and advertising purposes. You can manage your
            cookie preferences at any time through our cookie consent banner or by clicking
            <button
              type="button"
              class="underline text-[#C9A44A] hover:text-white transition"
              onclick="window.openPrivacySettings && window.openPrivacySettings()"
            >
              Privacy Settings
            </button>.
            Essential cookies necessary for the website to function are always active.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">5. Sharing Your Data</h2>
          <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share it with:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">afilma.com</strong> — to process payments and deliver purchased courses.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Google LLC</strong> — analytics and advertising (Google Analytics, Google Ads, Google Tag Manager).</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Meta Platforms, Inc.</strong> — advertising measurement (Meta Pixel / Conversions API).</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Email service providers</strong> — to send transactional and marketing emails.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-zinc-200">Legal authorities</strong> — when required by law or to protect our rights.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to provide our services and comply with legal
            obligations. Waitlist data is deleted after 24 months of inactivity. Customer records are retained
            for 5 years after the last purchase, in accordance with applicable tax and accounting regulations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">7. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
            <li>Object to or restrict certain processing activities.</li>
            <li>Data portability.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time (without affecting prior processing).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To exercise these rights, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:privacy@growthroom.co" class="text-[#C9A44A] hover:text-white transition underline">privacy@growthroom.co</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">8. International Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries outside your own. We ensure that any
            such transfers are subject to appropriate safeguards (e.g., Standard Contractual Clauses) consistent
            with applicable data protection law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are not directed at individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect
            personal data from minors. If you believe a minor has provided us with personal data, please
            contact us and we will delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes
            by posting the new policy on this page with an updated date. Continued use of our services after
            changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-base font-semibold text-white">11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions or concerns about this policy, contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:privacy@growthroom.co" class="text-[#C9A44A] hover:text-white transition underline">privacy@growthroom.co</a>
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 border-t border-white/8 pt-8 text-xs text-zinc-600">
        <p>
          © {new Date().getFullYear()} Growth Room. All rights reserved. ·
          <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-zinc-400 transition">Terms of Use</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
